<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-07-30T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-07-30T14:00:00-05:00" n="419" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.003/632: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Ruddock</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-30T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 30,
                                        1921—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>214. Your 256, July 12, noon.</p>
                        <p>You may join representatives of other Treaty Powers in accepting proposal
                            for a conference to consider a revision of tariff schedules. Such
                            revised tariff would have eventually to be incorporated in a convention
                            and submitted to the Senate for ratification.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>